article.description: — Jordan Goodwin had 23 points and 13 rebounds as Saint Louis stretched its home win streak to seven games, getting past UM Kansas City 62-46 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Goodwin leads Saint Louis past UM Kansas City 62-46
article.linkText: Goodwin leads Saint Louis past UM Kansas City 62-46
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- — Jordan Goodwin had 23 points and 13 rebounds as Saint Louis stretched its home win streak to seven games, getting past UM Kansas City 62-46 on Wednesday night. Goodwin made 9 of 11 foul shots. Javonte Perkins had 14 points for Saint Louis (7-1). Hasahn French added five assists and three blocks. Brandon McKissic had 18 points for the Roos (4-5). Josiah Allick added 13 points and nine rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
